g.title:
@politic_animal I'm sitting in a mobile home in on the very furthest point West in Europe (The Dingle Peninsula) hanging on your every post.
This is the very best of Twitter usage.

Fare well, questing BusPerson...

@politic_animal I havn't seen the backstory. Is there a record you have to beat (like 'quickest to visit every tube station')? 

Have you revealed where you are hoping to finish? Or are you taking bets?

If so, i'm going for Whitehaven.

@politic_animal There is nothing unfortunate about not arriving into the town of my birth at 3am ;) 

I hope you make Scotland then, but i'm a bit stumped where you will get a bus at 2am outside a major city, so North Newcastle it probably is!

The start of the annual #bus24fleelondon challenge?

@politic_animal Welcome to Lancashire - God's own county. And heading for Bolton - lovely stuff.

What a cracking day! 

Thanks for sharing.

@politic_animal My Lancastrian bias will obviously twitch, but I do accept that Leeds has splendid examples.

*pause*

It's no Rochdale...

@politic_animal Thanks to the very lovely designs of @GailMyerscough you can buy a variety of products celebrating Preston bus station! -
https://t.co/33CmTm8X8D

https://t.co/33CmTm8X8D

@politic_animal Greatly praised by the architect and writer Ian Nairn. The ramps to the car park are a symphony of spiralling concrete. It is magnificent. 
It was saved from demolition after a campaign by local people.
https://t.co/Ebom1GbhMU

@politic_animal Well done,  and thank you  for using a distance measurement I can understand, not that unintelligible imperial crap.

'Excuse me Mr English/USA Person, how far is the nearest supermarket please?
'Well it's about 15 & 3/4 horse hooves, and a virgins Wednesday toe nail away.'
